"title": "6735: repentance, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6735",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides examples to illustrate the importance of repentance for individuals and communities.</p>\n<h2>The repentance of individuals</h2>\n<h3>The call to personal repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:19\">2TI 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of individual repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:31-Num22:35\">NUM 22:31–22:35</a> <em>Balaam</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a> <em>David, after taking a census</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27-1Kgs21:29\">1KI 21:27–21:29</a> <em>Ahab</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:19\">2KI 22:19</a> <em>Josiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:6\">JOB 42:6</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:17\">PSA 51:1–51:17</a> <em>David, following his adultery with Bathsheba</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:21\">LUK 15:21</a> <em>the prodigal son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13\">LUK 18:13</a> <em>the tax collector in the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:75\">MAT 26:75</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:72\">MRK 14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:61-Luke22:62\">LUK 22:61–22:62</a> <em>Peter's sorrow after denying Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a> <em>Peter's confession and reinstatement</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:22-Acts8:24\">ACT 8:22–8:24</a> <em>Simon the sorcerer's repentance may not have been genuine.</em></p>\n<h2>Corporate repentance</h2>\n<h3>Examples of corporate repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:7-Jer18:8\">JER 18:7–18:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:1-Matt3:6\">MAT 3:1–3:6</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:1-Mark1:6\">MRK 1:1–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1-Luke3:6\">LUK 3:1–3:6</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:7\">NUM 21:7</a> <em>Israel in the desert</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:15-Judg10:16\">JDG 10:15–10:16</a> <em>Israel in the time of the judges</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:3-1Sam7:4\">1SA 7:3–7:4</a> <em>Israel, after asking for a king</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:22\">ISA 19:22</a> <em>Egypt turns to God in repentance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:32-Acts9:35\">ACT 9:32–9:35</a> <em>the people of Lydda and Sharon</em></p>\n<h3>Leaders encouraged corporate repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:1-2Kgs23:7\">2KI 23:1–23:7</a> <em>Josiah leads Judah in repentance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:8-2Chr15:15\">2CH 15:8–15:15</a> <em>Asa leads Judah in repentance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:6-2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:6–30:9</a> <em>Hezekiah leads Israel and Judah in repentance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:10-Ezra10:12\">EZR 10:10–10:12</a> <em>Following the exile, Ezra leads the Israelites in repentance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:6-Jonah3:8\">JON 3:6–3:8</a> <em>The king of Nineveh leads the people in repentance.</em></p>\n<h3>Corporate repentance within the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:4-Rev2:5\">REV 2:4–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:9-2Cor7:11\">2CO 7:9–7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14-Rev2:16\">REV 2:14–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20-Rev2:22\">REV 2:20–2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:3\">REV 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:19-Rev3:20\">REV 3:19–3:20</a></p>\n<h2>Symbols of repentance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27\">1KI 21:27</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:5\">JON 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:6\">1SA 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:21\">EZR 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:1\">NEH 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:9\">JER 36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:13-Joel1:14\">JOL 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12\">JOL 2:12</a></p>",
